&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6 Rehabilitation Physiotherapist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Respiratory Team at Wye Valley NHS Trust Hereford, who are looking to appoint a Band 6 Physiotherapist (26 hours a week) to join our expanding Pulmonary Rehabilitation Team. The Respiratory service offers high standards of care to a diverse population with both acute and chronic respiratory disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will play an active role in the delivery of the Pulmonary Rehabilitation service across the county, in hospital and community settings. They will also provide a specialist physiotherapy outpatient service to patients with a wide range of respiratory conditions, including COPD, bronchiectasis, pulmonary fibrosis and some neuromuscular conditions for cough augmentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate will have a high standard of clinical and communication skills to be able to work autonomously and as part of a team. Good interpersonal and organisational skills are essential for this post, along with a flexible approach and the ability to work under pressure. The candidate will also need to engage actively within the department and contribute to service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Respiratory experience is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit, please contact Vicki Howard, Specialist Respiratory Physiotherapist on 07813 406550 or via email vicki.howard@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
